==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Emeer
<hw>E*meer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar. <ets>em⟦imac⟧r</ets>,
<ets>am⟦imac⟧r</ets>, commander: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧mir</ets>. Cf.
<er>Admiral</er>, <er>Ameer</er>.]</ety> <def>An Arabian military
commander, independent chieftain, or ruler of a province; also, an
honorary title given to the descendants of Mohammed, in the line of his
daughter Fatima; among the Turks, likewise, a title of dignity, given to
certain high officials.</def></p>

<p><ent>Emeership</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Emirship</ent>⟦br⟧
